	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>It's very common when I transition someone from hourly to salary that they see a short term decrease in pay.  I've had several people refuse promotions for this reason.  I try to point out that the people in this situation typically are near thier top end earning potential as an hourly and the long term compensation potential of being salaried are worth the short term drop but some choose not to listen.  The rule of thumb at every place I've ever worked is to base the salary on people transitioning from hourly on their base, i.e. without unscheduled OT, wages adjusted for equity with others within their new pay grade.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
